# 📊 Visualization Strategy (MVP Level)

Keep it simple:

* Text values (mandatory)
* Basic visual (optional but impactful)

---

# 🎯 3. Per-Sensor Plan (IMPORTANT)

---

## 🔵 A. Motion Sensors

### 1. Accelerometer

* Values: X, Y, Z
* Visualization:

  * Moving dot (based on X/Y)
* Interpretation:

  * High values → "Movement detected"
  * Near zero → "Stable"

---

### 2. Gyroscope

* Values: X, Y, Z rotation
* Visualization:

  * Rotation indicator (text-based is fine for MVP)
* Interpretation:

  * Rapid change → "Rotating"

---

### 3. Rotation Vector (if available)

* Values: Orientation data
* Visualization:

  * Orientation text (Pitch / Roll / Yaw approx)
* Interpretation:

  * "Device tilted / flat"

---

## 🌍 B. Environmental Sensors

---

### 4. Light Sensor

* Value: Lux
* Visualization:

  * Background brightness change
* Interpretation:

  * <50 → Dark
  * 50–500 → Normal
  * > 500 → Bright

---

### 5. Proximity Sensor

* Value: distance
* Visualization:

  * Screen overlay (black/clear)
* Interpretation:

  * Near / Far

---

### 6. Pressure (Barometer)

* Value: hPa
* Visualization:

  * Text + simple progress bar
* Interpretation:

  * Show raw only (MVP)

---

## 📍 C. Position / Activity Sensors

---

### 7. Step Counter

* Value: steps
* Visualization:

  * Counter text
* Interpretation:

  * "Walking activity detected"

---

### 8. Step Detector

* Event-based
* Visualization:

  * Flash or increment
* Interpretation:

  * "Step detected"

---

## 🧠 D. Virtual Sensors

---

### 9. Linear Acceleration

* Values: X, Y, Z
* Interpretation:

  * Motion without gravity

---

### 10. Gravity Sensor

* Values: X, Y, Z
* Visualization:

  * Direction arrow (optional)

---

# ⚠️ 4. Unsupported / Missing Sensors

## Handling Strategy

```text id="9rfk3t"
if (sensor == null)
   → Show "Not Available"
```

---

# ⚡ 5. Performance Rules

* Use:

```java id="8l1mdx"
SensorManager.SENSOR_DELAY_NORMAL
```

* Avoid:

  * High-frequency updates (battery drain)

---

# 🧠 6. Data Processing (Minimal)

## Optional Smoothing

```text id="2y9hjq"
filtered = alpha * new + (1-alpha) * old
```

👉 Only if values are too noisy

---

# 🔄 7. Data Flow

```text id="x3h2bd"
Sensor → SensorEvent → Values → UI Update → Interpretation
```

---

# 🧩 8. Code Flow Summary

```text id="r6c1ok"
onCreate():
   get sensor type
   initialize UI

onResume():
   register listener

onSensorChanged():
   update values
   update visualization
   update interpretation

onPause():
   unregister listener
```

---

# ⚠️ 9. MVP Constraints

* No advanced graphics (no OpenGL)
* No ML-based interpretation
* No background tracking
* No data storage

---

# 🔥 10. What Makes This Module Solid

* Works on most devices
* Handles missing sensors
* Clear structure (List → Detail)
* Extensible for future upgrades

---

# 📌 Final Outcome

User can:

* See all available sensors
* Tap and explore each
* Understand behavior in real-time

